CSS has 3 types-> INLINE,INTERNAL AND EXTERNAL

1.INLINE
this type of css is used for a single line only
sample code

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Inline</title>
</head>

<body>
<h1 style="color: blue">Style Me in Blue</h1>

</body>

</html>

2.INTERNAL
this type of css is used for a single webpage only
sample code

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Internal</title>
</head>

<body>
<h1>Style Me in Red!</h1>
<style>
  html{
    color: red;
  }
</style>
</body>

</html>

3.EXTERNAL
this type of css is used in majority cases
can be used for multiple pages
sample code
#to be written in an html file and linked to another css file
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Internal</title>
</head>

<body>
<h1>Style Me in Red!</h1>
<style>
  html{
    color: red;
  }
</style>
</body>

</html>

#to be written in a css file
html{
    color: green ;
}
